1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:03,112
JavaScript's class syntax supports inheritance

2
00:00:03,487 --> 00:00:07,575
allowing one class to inherit properties and methods from another

3
00:00:07,975 --> 00:00:12,075
This inheritance is implemented using the 'extends' keyword

4
00:00:12,463 --> 00:00:17,225
providing a way to create a hierarchy of classes and reuse code efficiently

5
00:00:17,625 --> 00:00:21,750
This feature is essential for creating complex applications efficiently

6
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:26,725
as it enables developers to build on existing code without duplication

